column5: hello everyone,  today i become member and from now on i will share with you my up's and down's  from my experience. i have a question..in the mid february i will go ice fishing on lake nepewassi. has anybody been there? what kind of fish can you catch there? thanks...and have a good week!!!

Look for Walleye and Pike on the east shore of Barlow Bay in front of the rock cuts..  There are some islands in front of Vacationland that hold Walleye and Pike...  Good Luck... Nepewassi is a very pressured lake  be very patient.  RFS
